'''Caste''' is a form of [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_stratification social stratification] characterized by [//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endogamy endogamy], hereditary transmission of a lifestyle which often includes an occupation, status in a hierarchy, and customary social interaction and exclusion.{{Sfn|Scott|Marshall|2005|p=66}}{{Sfn|Winthrop|1991|pp=27–30}} Its paradigmatic ethnographic example is the division of society into rigid social groups, with roots in ancient history and persisting until today.{{Sfn|Béteille|2002|p=66}} Sociologists and anthropologists can study the social divisions existing in various countries by using the caste-like systems as an analogical basis for research. The term caste-system is also applied to non-human populations like ants and bees.
